100
00:08:32,613 --> 00:08:35,605
Incan matrimonial head masks.

101
00:08:36,533 --> 00:08:40,412
- Any money in Incan matrimonial...?
- Head masks. Some.

102
00:08:40,613 --> 00:08:44,492
Don't let him fool you.
There's loads if you can move them.

103
00:08:44,693 --> 00:08:48,003
I'll take one. But you can't.

104
00:08:48,213 --> 00:08:51,205
- My fence was confident.
- You don't need a fence.

105
00:08:51,413 --> 00:08:54,803
- Some people lack vision.
- Everybody in cellblock E.

106
00:08:55,013 --> 00:08:56,731
That's $500.

107
00:08:57,453 --> 00:09:01,128
- What's the first lesson in poker?
- Never bet on the...

108
00:09:01,373 --> 00:09:03,841
- Leave emotion at the door.
- Right, Topher.

109
00:09:04,053 --> 00:09:06,772
Today's lesson:
How to draw out the bluff.

110
00:09:06,973 --> 00:09:09,043
That much money, this early... .

111
00:09:09,253 --> 00:09:12,563
He has nothing better than
a pair of face cards.

112
00:09:12,813 --> 00:09:14,166
Barry?

113
00:09:17,013 --> 00:09:18,287
All right.

114
00:09:18,733 --> 00:09:20,451
I fold.

115
00:09:22,493 --> 00:09:24,927
- Josh?
- Don't worry, I'm game.

116
00:09:25,133 --> 00:09:29,684
I will see your $500
and I will raise you another...

117
00:09:30,213 --> 00:09:33,569
...$500 of my own.
- That's a very handsome bet.

118
00:09:33,813 --> 00:09:39,206
But don't push him too high, too fast.
Keep him on the leash.

119
00:09:39,413 --> 00:09:41,324
- Holly?
- Call.

120
00:09:42,173 --> 00:09:43,401
Call.

121
00:09:44,213 --> 00:09:45,851
And I'll call.

122
00:09:49,173 --> 00:09:52,882
I'll see your $500
and raise you $2000.

123
00:09:53,613 --> 00:09:56,889
Guys, you do what you like.
That's a lot of money.

124
00:09:57,093 --> 00:10:02,087
I'm staying in. He's trying to buy
his way out of his bluff.

125
00:10:03,333 --> 00:10:05,972
- Josh?
- Two.

126
00:10:11,053 --> 00:10:12,452
Thattagirl. Call.

127
00:10:13,013 --> 00:10:15,527
- Call.
- Call.

128
00:10:18,293 --> 00:10:19,965
Let's see them.

129
00:10:20,173 --> 00:10:25,805
I'm not sure what four nines does,
but the ace, I think, is pretty high.

130
00:10:26,893 --> 00:10:29,088
Thanks for the tip on bluffing.

131
00:10:29,693 --> 00:10:34,448
Hey, Topher! How about an autograph?
Come on, real quick.

132
00:10:49,533 --> 00:10:53,242
- God, I'm bored.
- You look bored.

133
00:10:53,973 --> 00:10:57,522
How was the clink?
You get the cookies I sent?

134
00:10:57,973 --> 00:11:00,885
Why do you think
I came to see you first?

135
00:11:01,693 --> 00:11:03,923
- So tell me.
- It's tricky.

136
00:11:04,213 --> 00:11:08,604
It's never been done before.
It'll need planning and a large crew.

137
00:11:09,493 --> 00:11:12,724
- Guns?
- Not quite. High security. The take...

138
00:11:13,173 --> 00:11:14,925
- The target?
- Eight figures.

139
00:11:15,133 --> 00:11:16,964
What's the target?

140
00:11:18,373 --> 00:11:21,410
When was the last time
you were in Vegas?

141
00:11:21,613 --> 00:11:24,286
You want to knock over a casino?

142
00:11:37,013 --> 00:11:38,924
The vault at the Bellagio.

143
00:11:43,573 --> 00:11:47,407
If I'm reading this right,
and I'd like to think I am...

144
00:11:48,053 --> 00:11:52,171
...this is probably the least
accessible vault ever designed.

145
00:11:53,253 --> 00:11:55,164
You said three casinos?

146
00:11:55,413 --> 00:12:01,124
These feed into the Mirage and MGM
Grand, but every dime ends up there.

147
00:12:01,973 --> 00:12:04,533
The Bellagio and the Mirage.

148
00:12:04,733 --> 00:12:08,726
- These are Terry Benedict's places.
- Yes, they are.

149
00:12:08,933 --> 00:12:11,686
- Think he'll mind?
- More than somewhat.

150
00:12:11,893 --> 00:12:15,806
You'd need at least 12 guys
doing a combination of cons.

151
00:12:16,013 --> 00:12:17,605
Like what, you think?

152
00:12:17,813 --> 00:12:22,841
Off the top of my head, I'd say you're
looking at a Boesky, a Jim Brown...

153
00:12:23,053 --> 00:12:25,362
...a Miss Daisy and a Leon Spinks.

154
00:12:25,613 --> 00:12:29,322
Not to mention the biggest
Ella Fitzgerald ever.

155
00:12:29,533 --> 00:12:32,286
Where will you get
the money to back this?

156
00:12:32,493 --> 00:12:35,485
Hit these three casinos,
we'll get our bankroll.

157
00:12:35,693 --> 00:12:38,002
Benedict's got a list of enemies.

158
00:12:38,253 --> 00:12:41,928
But enemies with loose
cash and nothing to lose?

159
00:12:45,013 --> 00:12:46,526
- Reuben.
- Reuben.

160
00:12:46,813 --> 00:12:48,166
Hey.

161
00:12:49,413 --> 00:12:51,688
Oscar, lower it a bit,
would you?

162
00:12:52,213 --> 00:12:55,125
Sorry. You guys done?
Find what you want?

163
00:12:55,333 --> 00:12:58,291
We'll take these for the night
to make copies.

164
00:12:58,493 --> 00:13:01,371
- Whatever you need.
- Appreciate it.

165
00:13:08,533 --> 00:13:09,761
What?

166
00:13:11,253 --> 00:13:12,732
I need a reason.

167
00:13:13,493 --> 00:13:15,848
And don't say money. Why do this?

168
00:13:16,053 --> 00:13:18,089
Why not do it?

169
00:13:23,013 --> 00:13:26,688
I just left the joint after
losing four years of my life...

170
00:13:26,893 --> 00:13:29,851
...and you're cold-decking
Teen Beat cover boys.

171
00:13:31,733 --> 00:13:33,803
Because the house always wins.

172
00:13:34,013 --> 00:13:37,050
Play long enough,
the house takes you.

173
00:13:37,253 --> 00:13:42,725
Unless, when that perfect hand comes,
you bet big. Then you take the house.

174
00:13:45,573 --> 00:13:48,292
- You practiced that speech?
- Did I rush it?

175
00:13:48,533 --> 00:13:50,888
It was good.
The Teen Beat thing was harsh.

176
00:13:54,693 --> 00:13:56,763
I wonder what Reuben will say.

177
00:13:57,773 --> 00:14:00,207
You're out of your damn minds!

178
00:14:02,053 --> 00:14:03,566
You're both of you nuts!

179
00:14:03,813 --> 00:14:09,012
I know more about casino security
than any man. I invented it.

180
00:14:09,213 --> 00:14:11,010
And it cannot be beaten.

181
00:14:11,213 --> 00:14:14,250
They got cameras and watchers,
they got locks.

182
00:14:14,453 --> 00:14:16,205
They got timers, vaults.

183
00:14:16,533 --> 00:14:19,843
They got enough armed
personnel to occupy Paris!

184
00:14:20,853 --> 00:14:22,969
Okay, bad example.

185
00:14:23,213 --> 00:14:24,851
It's never been tried.

186
00:14:25,813 --> 00:14:30,250
It's been tried.
A few guys even came close.

187
00:14:30,453 --> 00:14:34,002
You know the three most successful
robberies in Vegas?

188
00:14:34,213 --> 00:14:36,124
Number three, the bronze medal.

189
00:14:36,333 --> 00:14:39,325
Pencil neck grabs
a lockbox at the Horseshoe.

190
00:14:39,533 --> 00:14:41,728
Grab the guy in the suit!

191
00:14:42,453 --> 00:14:46,082
He got two steps closer
to the door than anyone before.

192
00:14:46,293 --> 00:14:47,408
Leave the money!

193
00:14:47,613 --> 00:14:49,490
Second most successful robbery:

194
00:14:49,733 --> 00:14:54,011
The Flamingo in '71. This guy
actually tasted fresh oxygen...

195
00:14:54,213 --> 00:14:56,169
...before they grabbed him.

196
00:14:56,693 --> 00:15:00,971
Of course, he was breathing out
of a hose for the next three weeks.

197
00:15:01,173 --> 00:15:02,891
Goddamn hippie.

198
00:15:03,253 --> 00:15:08,247
And the closest any man has come
to robbing a Las Vegas casino...

199
00:15:08,653 --> 00:15:11,565
...was outside of Caesars in '87.

200
00:15:12,533 --> 00:15:13,648
He came...

201
00:15:14,613 --> 00:15:15,887
...he grabbed...

202
00:15:16,733 --> 00:15:18,485
...they conquered.

203
00:15:23,453 --> 00:15:27,890
But what am I saying?
You guys are pros. The best.

204
00:15:28,213 --> 00:15:31,046
I'm sure you can make
it out of the casino.

205
00:15:31,253 --> 00:15:33,403
Of course, lest we forget...

206
00:15:33,613 --> 00:15:38,687
...once you're out, you're still
in the middle of the fucking desert!

207
00:15:39,093 --> 00:15:40,526
You're right.
He's right.

208
00:15:40,733 --> 00:15:43,406
Our eyes were bigger
than our stomachs.

209
00:15:43,613 --> 00:15:46,650
- That's what it is. Ego.
- Yeah, blah, blah.

