313
00:24:54,053 --> 00:24:57,966
Saul makes 10.
Ten should do it, don't you think?

314
00:24:59,093 --> 00:25:01,004
You think we need one more?

315
00:25:02,053 --> 00:25:04,806
You think we need one more.

316
00:25:05,733 --> 00:25:08,008
All right, we'll get one more.

317
00:26:22,773 --> 00:26:25,970
Hello, Linus. Whose is this?

318
00:26:27,253 --> 00:26:30,290
- Who are you?
- A friend of Bobby Caldwell's.

319
00:26:31,493 --> 00:26:34,769
You're either in or out.
Right now.

320
00:26:37,573 --> 00:26:41,532
- What is it?
- It's a plane ticket. A job offer.

321
00:26:42,733 --> 00:26:46,282
- You're pretty trusting.
- Bobby has faith in you.

322
00:26:46,533 --> 00:26:48,728
Fathers are like that.

323
00:26:49,093 --> 00:26:52,722
He didn't tell you? He doesn't
want me trading on his name.

324
00:26:52,933 --> 00:26:55,686
Do this job,
he'll be trading on yours.

325
00:26:55,893 --> 00:26:59,283
Don't, and you can go back
to feeling up stockbrokers.

326
00:26:59,493 --> 00:27:01,768
Can you get the check, please?

327
00:27:04,973 --> 00:27:06,964
That's the best lift you've made yet.

328
00:27:07,373 --> 00:27:08,965
Las Vegas?

329
00:27:09,173 --> 00:27:10,811
America's playground.

330
00:27:54,853 --> 00:27:57,925
Did you guys get a group rate,
or something?

331
00:28:03,973 --> 00:28:06,362
Saul, do you get out to Utah much?

332
00:28:07,933 --> 00:28:10,128
Not as often as I'd like.

333
00:28:10,453 --> 00:28:15,129
Check it out. I think you'd dig Provo.
You could do well there.

334
00:28:15,413 --> 00:28:17,165
I'll look into it.

335
00:28:18,133 --> 00:28:22,570
Welcome to Las Vegas.
Has everybody eaten? Good.

336
00:28:22,933 --> 00:28:24,730
Everybody sober?

337
00:28:25,253 --> 00:28:29,565
Close enough. Before we start,
nobody's on the line yet.

338
00:28:29,813 --> 00:28:34,204
What I'm about to propose is highly
lucrative and highly dangerous.

339
00:28:34,413 --> 00:28:37,052
If that's not your brand of vodka...

340
00:28:37,253 --> 00:28:41,804
...eat as much as you like and have
a safe journey. No hard feelings.

341
00:28:42,013 --> 00:28:43,685
Otherwise, come with me.

342
00:28:52,733 --> 00:28:54,769
You're Bobby Caldwell's kid?

343
00:28:56,213 --> 00:28:59,011
- From Chicago?
- Yeah.

344
00:29:00,053 --> 00:29:02,408
- You like it there?
- Yeah.

345
00:29:02,613 --> 00:29:06,492
That's wonderful.
Get in the goddamn house.

346
00:29:15,773 --> 00:29:18,606
The 3000 block
of Las Vegas Boulevard...

347
00:29:18,973 --> 00:29:22,204
...also known as the Bellagio,
Mirage and MGM Grand.

348
00:29:22,453 --> 00:29:26,446
They're three of the most
profitable casinos in Las Vegas.

349
00:29:29,013 --> 00:29:31,447
This is the Bellagio vault, located...

350
00:29:31,693 --> 00:29:34,287
...beneath 200 feet of solid earth.

351
00:29:34,493 --> 00:29:39,362
It safeguards every dime that passes
through each of the three casinos.

352
00:29:39,573 --> 00:29:42,531
- We're gonna rob it.
- Smash-and-grab job?

353
00:29:42,773 --> 00:29:45,082
Slightly more complicated than that.

354
00:29:45,893 --> 00:29:47,326
Well, yeah.

355
00:29:48,013 --> 00:29:52,928
This is courtesy of Frank Catton,
a new dealer at the Bellagio.

356
00:29:53,213 --> 00:29:54,532
Bad news first.

357
00:29:54,773 --> 00:29:58,891
This place houses a security system
rivaling most nuclear silos.

358
00:29:59,093 --> 00:30:03,962
First, we have to get in the casino
cages, which takes more than a smile.

359
00:30:04,173 --> 00:30:06,562
Next, through these doors...

360
00:30:06,813 --> 00:30:11,045
...each one requiring a different
code changed every 12 hours.

361
00:30:11,253 --> 00:30:14,802
Past those, the elevator.
Here's where it gets tricky.

362
00:30:15,013 --> 00:30:19,484
- It won't move without fingerprint I.D.
- Which we can't fake.

363
00:30:19,733 --> 00:30:24,488
And vocal confirmation from the system
within the Bellagio and the vault.

364
00:30:24,733 --> 00:30:26,166
Which we won't get.

365
00:30:26,373 --> 00:30:29,285
The elevator shaft is rigged
with sensors.

366
00:30:29,493 --> 00:30:34,123
If we override the lift, the exit
would lock and we'd be trapped.

367
00:30:34,373 --> 00:30:37,604
Once we get down the shaft,
it's a piece of cake.

368
00:30:37,853 --> 00:30:41,050
Just two more guards with Uzis...

369
00:30:41,333 --> 00:30:44,882
...and the most elaborate
vault door ever conceived.

370
00:30:45,493 --> 00:30:47,085
Any questions?

371
00:30:49,853 --> 00:30:51,571
Tunneling's out. There are...

372
00:30:51,813 --> 00:30:56,443
...sensors monitoring the ground.
If a groundhog nested, they'd know.

373
00:30:57,013 --> 00:30:59,811
- Anyone else?
- You mentioned good news?

374
00:31:00,013 --> 00:31:03,244
Yeah. The Nevada Gaming
Commission requires...

375
00:31:03,453 --> 00:31:07,844
...a casino to keep enough cash
to cover every chip on the floor.

376
00:31:08,053 --> 00:31:11,728
That means on a weekday, by law,
it must carry...

377
00:31:11,933 --> 00:31:14,686
...between $60 and $ 70 million
in cash and coin.

378
00:31:14,893 --> 00:31:18,886
On the weekend, between 80 and 90
million. On a fight night...

379
00:31:19,093 --> 00:31:22,051
...in two weeks,
the night we're robbing it...

380
00:31:22,253 --> 00:31:25,484
...$ 150 million,
without breaking a sweat.

381
00:31:26,293 --> 00:31:29,569
There are 11 of us,
each with an equal share.

382
00:31:30,053 --> 00:31:31,327
You do the math.

383
00:31:31,853 --> 00:31:32,922
Exactly.

384
00:31:33,133 --> 00:31:34,452
I have a question.

385
00:31:34,973 --> 00:31:38,886
Say we get into the cage
and through the security doors...

386
00:31:39,093 --> 00:31:41,368
...down the elevator
we can't move...

387
00:31:41,573 --> 00:31:45,566
...past the guards with the guns,
into the vault we can't open...

388
00:31:46,093 --> 00:31:50,211
- Without being seen by cameras.
- Sorry, I forgot to mention that.

389
00:31:50,493 --> 00:31:53,007
Yeah, well, say we do all that...

390
00:31:53,213 --> 00:31:57,684
...we're just supposed to walk out
of there with $ 150 million...

391
00:31:57,893 --> 00:32:00,327
...without getting stopped?

392
00:32:05,093 --> 00:32:06,367
Yeah.

393
00:32:08,573 --> 00:32:11,565
Oh. Okay.

394
00:32:18,613 --> 00:32:22,288
First task: reconnaissance.
I want to know what goes on...

395
00:32:22,493 --> 00:32:25,246
...in all casinos,
from the dealers ' rotation...

396
00:32:25,453 --> 00:32:31,244
...to the path of cash carts. I want
to know everything about every guard.

397
00:32:32,573 --> 00:32:37,408
Find out where they're from,
nicknames, how they take their coffee.

398
00:32:37,693 --> 00:32:40,685
She dances at Crazy Horse Too,
to pay for school.

399
00:32:40,893 --> 00:32:44,010
- I think she really likes me.
- Cool.

400
00:32:49,173 --> 00:32:52,768
Know these casinos.
They were built to keep people in.

401
00:32:52,973 --> 00:32:54,691
Know the quick routes out.

402
00:32:54,893 --> 00:32:58,329
- He went through at 10:44.
- 10:46. Get a watch that works.

403
00:32:58,533 --> 00:33:01,923
- You make me sick, dude. It's 10:44.
- 10:46.

404
00:33:06,533 --> 00:33:08,285
Second task: power.

405
00:33:08,813 --> 00:33:13,125
Fight night, we throw the switch
on Sin City. It's Basher's show.

406
00:33:13,333 --> 00:33:16,052
You want broke, blind or bedlam?

407
00:33:16,253 --> 00:33:19,484
- How about all three?
- Right, it's done.

408
00:33:20,853 --> 00:33:22,571
Third task: surveillance.

409
00:33:22,813 --> 00:33:25,691
Security has an eye
and an ear on everything.

410
00:33:25,893 --> 00:33:28,282
We want an eye and ear on them.
Livingston?

411
00:33:28,493 --> 00:33:31,963
Not the least accessible system
I've seen, but close.

412
00:33:32,173 --> 00:33:35,404
- There's no closed-circuit I can tap?
- No.

413
00:33:35,613 --> 00:33:40,641
Then it's definitely a black bag job.
They employ an in-house technician?

414
00:33:40,853 --> 00:33:43,492
Two. And one of them is lonely.

415
00:33:57,333 --> 00:34:00,370
Thanks, Charmaine.
I'll return it in an hour.

416
00:34:00,573 --> 00:34:04,725
- Say hi to your mom for me.
- Say it yourself. She's on-stage soon.

417
00:34:27,173 --> 00:34:28,128
