01:26:22,055 --> 01:26:25,604
- You gonna answer that?
- I don't have a cell phone.

962
01:26:29,495 --> 01:26:31,133
This isn't mine.

963
01:26:32,815 --> 01:26:34,373
See who it is.

964
01:26:36,295 --> 01:26:39,173
- Hello?
- May I have a word with Mr. Benedict?

965
01:26:39,375 --> 01:26:40,854
It's for you.

966
01:26:45,255 --> 01:26:48,725
- Who the hell is this?
- The man who 's robbing you.

967
01:26:53,455 --> 01:26:58,575
- What's going on in the vault?
- Nothing, sir. It's all normal.

968
01:26:58,775 --> 01:27:00,208
Show me.

969
01:27:02,135 --> 01:27:05,093
- You're mistaken.
- Watching your monitors?

970
01:27:05,295 --> 01:27:07,525
Okay, keep watching.

971
01:27:16,935 --> 01:27:19,847
In this town,
luck can change that quickly.

972
01:27:20,055 --> 01:27:23,331
- Find out how much money's down there.
- Yes, sir.

973
01:27:39,575 --> 01:27:40,894
Tess?

974
01:27:41,535 --> 01:27:43,093
Tess?

975
01:27:43,935 --> 01:27:45,607
Perhaps you should... .

976
01:27:45,935 --> 01:27:47,766
Perhaps I should what?

977
01:27:48,615 --> 01:27:52,324
It would be better if you weren't
around here for this.

978
01:27:59,975 --> 01:28:02,569
All right, you proved your point.

979
01:28:02,775 --> 01:28:07,690
You broke into my vault.
Congratulations. You're a dead man.

980
01:28:07,895 --> 01:28:12,491
- Maybe.
- Maybe? May I ask how you will leave?

981
01:28:12,815 --> 01:28:16,444
You think I'll let you
take my money out my casino doors?

982
01:28:16,655 --> 01:28:20,648
- No. You'll carry it out for us.
- Why would I do that?

983
01:28:20,855 --> 01:28:22,413
Look at your monitor.

984
01:28:24,095 --> 01:28:28,486
As your manager's probably reporting,
you have over $ 160 million...

985
01:28:28,735 --> 01:28:32,648
...in your vault tonight.
We're only packing up half that.

986
01:28:32,895 --> 01:28:36,934
The other half we're leaving,
booby-trapped, as a hostage.

987
01:28:37,215 --> 01:28:41,254
You let our $80 million go,
and you get to keep yours.

988
01:28:41,455 --> 01:28:44,925
You try and stop us,
we'll blow both cashloads.

989
01:28:48,535 --> 01:28:54,292
You can lose $80 million secretly
or lose $ 160 million publicly.

990
01:28:54,495 --> 01:28:55,769
Your decision.
Hi.

991
01:29:06,615 --> 01:29:08,173
Make the call.

992
01:29:13,295 --> 01:29:15,047
911 emergency response.

993
01:29:16,295 --> 01:29:19,207
- Where's Danny?
- He's fine. He's in good form.

994
01:29:19,415 --> 01:29:23,124
- He asks that you go up and watch TV.
- He does?

995
01:29:23,535 --> 01:29:28,131
We have three men with explosives
who have taken control of our vault.

996
01:29:30,815 --> 01:29:32,771
- Okay.
- It's okay.

997
01:29:33,175 --> 01:29:34,767
- You have a deal.
- I promise.

998
01:29:34,975 --> 01:29:37,489
Fantastic.
Here's what you do:

999
01:29:38,935 --> 01:29:42,564
The guys in the vault will put
six bags in the elevator.

1000
01:29:42,815 --> 01:29:44,612
It will rise to your cages.

1001
01:29:44,855 --> 01:29:48,814
Three of your guards will carry
the bags into the casino.

1002
01:29:49,215 --> 01:29:54,494
If they take more than 20 seconds
to reach the floor, or there's a switch...

1003
01:29:54,735 --> 01:29:57,169
...we'll blow all the money.

1004
01:29:58,895 --> 01:30:02,126
- He's in the casino by the slots.
- Of course I am.

1005
01:30:02,335 --> 01:30:07,534
I'm staying in your hotel.
I have two words for you: mini bar.

1006
01:30:09,215 --> 01:30:11,683
Once the guards
hit the casino floor...

1007
01:30:11,895 --> 01:30:17,094
...a white van will pull up outside.
Your guards will load the rear.

1008
01:30:17,295 --> 01:30:22,369
If anyone so much as approaches
the driver's door, we'll blow everything.

1009
01:30:23,735 --> 01:30:28,286
When I hear the van is away and
the money is secure, my men will leave.

1010
01:30:28,495 --> 01:30:31,931
Once their safety is confirmed,
you get your vault.

1011
01:30:32,495 --> 01:30:34,326
The S.W.A.T. team is here.

1012
01:30:35,895 --> 01:30:37,408
All right.

1013
01:30:37,615 --> 01:30:42,564
Now, I have complied with your
every request. Would you agree?

1014
01:30:42,815 --> 01:30:44,043
I would.

1015
01:30:44,495 --> 01:30:47,248
Good. Because now
I have one of my own:

1016
01:30:48,055 --> 01:30:51,684
Run and hide, asshole.
Run and hide.

1017
01:30:51,895 --> 01:30:56,730
If you're picked up buying a $ 100,000
sports car in Newport Beach...

1018
01:30:56,935 --> 01:31:02,009
...I'll be disappointed. I want my
people to find you, and when they do...

1019
01:31:02,215 --> 01:31:05,844
...rest assured, we won't
hand you over to the police.

1020
01:31:06,055 --> 01:31:10,606
So, my advice to you again
is this: run and hide.

1021
01:31:11,295 --> 01:31:13,570
That is all that I ask.

1022
01:31:35,055 --> 01:31:39,446
Mr. Benedict, our guys say that
van is headed for McCarran Airport.

1023
01:31:39,655 --> 01:31:43,091
I want my vault back
before that van hits the tarmac.

1024
01:31:53,015 --> 01:31:55,529
Night goggles on.
Prepare to cut power.

1025
01:31:58,935 --> 01:32:00,129
Ready.

1026
01:32:02,855 --> 01:32:04,607
Cutting power now.

1027
01:32:06,895 --> 01:32:08,010
Do it.

1028
01:32:09,735 --> 01:32:11,965
Breaching elevator doors now.

1029
01:32:12,535 --> 01:32:15,845
We have two guards,
bound, unconscious.

1030
01:32:16,375 --> 01:32:17,524
Wait a minute.

1031
01:32:17,775 --> 01:32:19,527
Guys! Guys!
Someone's here!

1032
01:32:19,775 --> 01:32:22,164
- Take him down, now!
- I got him!

1033
01:32:23,855 --> 01:32:26,813
- Lights! We need power now!
- Give it to him.

1034
01:32:37,935 --> 01:32:39,766
What's going on?
Talk to me.

1035
01:32:39,975 --> 01:32:43,968
It appears an explosive incendiary
device has been detonated.

1036
01:32:44,175 --> 01:32:47,724
Continuing search for survivors.

1037
01:32:47,935 --> 01:32:50,654
Tell them to take the van.
I'll be there.

1038
01:32:50,895 --> 01:32:53,853
And find out how they
hooked into my system!

1039
01:32:54,055 --> 01:32:55,534
Yes, sir.

1040
01:33:13,095 --> 01:33:16,292
Get out of the van, now.
Now!

1041
01:33:20,615 --> 01:33:22,287
Tires. Tires.

1042
01:33:38,455 --> 01:33:40,491
Our search yielded no suspects.

1043
01:33:40,735 --> 01:33:44,808
Nor can we determine how they
entered or exited the premises.

1044
01:33:47,215 --> 01:33:49,888
- Take your men out.
- May I suggest...?

1045
01:33:50,095 --> 01:33:51,528
Now.

1046
01:33:51,895 --> 01:33:54,853
It's your vault.
Blue team, move it out!

1047
01:34:03,055 --> 01:34:05,250
Walsh, where are
we with the van?

1048
01:34:22,815 --> 01:34:25,568
I just want to try
something for a second.

1049
01:34:26,815 --> 01:34:29,045
There's nobody inside.

1050
01:34:30,655 --> 01:34:35,410
- I'm sorry. Did you want to get in?
- Enough monkey business.

1051
01:34:35,615 --> 01:34:37,173
Do it already.

1052
01:34:51,935 --> 01:34:54,927
Mr. Benedict.
We took the van, sir.

1053
01:34:55,135 --> 01:34:56,124
And?

1054
01:34:56,335 --> 01:34:59,532
They say there was no
money in the bags, sir.

1055
01:34:59,775 --> 01:35:01,254
What do you mean?

1056
01:35:01,455 --> 01:35:06,006
They say the bags were filled
with fliers, sir. For hookers.

1057
01:35:12,095 --> 01:35:13,164
Walsh?

1058
01:35:13,495 --> 01:35:15,247
Cue the tape to the robbery.

1059
01:35:17,735 --> 01:35:20,169
Yes, sir.
I'm looking at the tape now.

1060
01:35:20,895 --> 01:35:24,285
Does it say "Bellagio"
on the vault floor?

1061
01:35:24,495 --> 01:35:27,009
No, it doesn't.
I don't understand.

1062
01:35:29,255 --> 01:35:31,132
We had it installed Tuesday.

1063
01:35:31,335 --> 01:35:34,850
The images we saw of those
men robbing us was a tape.

1064
01:35:35,135 --> 01:35:36,329
What?

1065
01:35:38,255 --> 01:35:41,964
It was staged. Somebody made
a duplicate of my vault.

1066
01:35:42,175 --> 01:35:46,134
What we saw on the monitor
wasn't actually happening.

1067
01:35:47,175 --> 01:35:50,884
I don 't understand.
What happened to all that money?

1068
01:36:01,015 --> 01:36:02,243
Make the call.

1069
01:36:09,615 --> 01:36:11,526
911 emergency response.

1070
01:36:15,135 --> 01:36:17,171
- Night goggles on.
- Clear.

1071
01:36:17,375 --> 01:36:18,808
Prepare to cut power.

1072
01:36:23,735 --> 01:36:26,169
Breaching elevator doors now.

1073
01:36:26,535 --> 01:36:29,607
We have two guards,
bound, unconscious.

1074
01:36:29,815 --> 01:36:30,930
Wait a minute.

1075
01:36:31,135 --> 01:36:32,853
Guys! Guys!
Someone's here!

1076
01:36:33,135 --> 01:36:35,774
- Take him down, now!
- I got him!

1077
01:37:22,455 --> 01:37:23,524
Open the door.

1078
01:37:29,615 --> 01:37:33,403
Hey, Benedict.
How's the other fight going?

1079
01:37:38,895 --> 01:37:39,930
Pick him up.

1080
01:37:48,815 --> 01:37:50,646
Did you have a hand in this?

1081
01:37:51,855 --> 01:37:54,085
Did I have my hand in what?

1082
01:37:58,535 --> 01:38:00,491
I'll ask you one more time.

1083
01:38:00,735 --> 01:38:02,885
Did you have a hand in this?

1084
01:38:05,655 --> 01:38:09,489
Benedict, I have no idea
what you're talking about.

1085
01:38:13,775 --> 01:38:15,128
Okay.

1086
01:38:16,335 --> 01:38:18,132
You're free to go.

1087
01:38:20,135 --> 01:38:21,807
Show him out.

1088
01:38:28,175 --> 01:38:30,735
- Hello.
- Turn to channel 88.

1089
01:38:30,935 --> 01:38:32,607
Who is this?

1090
01:38:41,255 --> 01:38:43,849
What happened, Benedict?
You get robbed?

1091
01:38:44,055 --> 01:38:45,488
Stop.

1092
01:38:56,055 --> 01:38:58,410
I'll give you one last chance.

1093
01:38:59,455 --> 01:39:00,649
Where's my money?

1094
01:39:00,855 --> 01:39:03,892
What if I said you could
get your money back...

1095
01:39:04,735 --> 01:39:06,646
...if you give up Tess?

1096
01:39:07,215 --> 01:39:09,092
What would you say?

1097
01:39:12,015 --> 01:39:13,130
I would say yes.

1098
01:39:17,975 --> 01:39:19,203
All right.

1099
01:39:21,135 --> 01:39:24,047
I know a guy.
We were in the joint together.

1100
01:39:24,255 --> 01:39:28,328
Anybody pulls a job in the Western
U. S., he knows about it.

1101
01:39:28,935 --> 01:39:32,769
Give me 72 hours, I'll find
out who took your money.

1102
01:39:36,935 --> 01:39:38,891
You know a guy.

1103
01:39:41,495 --> 01:39:46,205
Contact the police. I'm sure he's
in violation of his parole.

1104
01:39:46,415 --> 01:39:47,848
Yes, sir.

1105
01:40:12,655 --> 01:40:14,088
Tess.

1106
01:40:15,935 --> 01:40:17,414
Tess.

1107
01:40:18,015 --> 01:40:20,449
You of all people
should know, Terry.

1108
01:40:20,655 --> 01:40:24,330
In your hotel, there's
always someone watching.

1109
01:42:00,655 --> 01:42:02,168
Wait!

1110
01:42:02,935 --> 01:42:04,209
Wait!

1111
01:42:05,615 --> 01:42:08,493
Wait, that's my husband!

1112
01:42:11,775 --> 01:42:15,051
- Danny.
- Tess, I told you...

1113
01:42:16,255 --> 01:42:18,166
...I knew what I was doing.

1114
01:42:19,015 --> 01:42:20,448
I didn't.

1115
01:42:20,655 --> 01:42:22,373
All right, let's go.

1116
01:42:23,535 --> 01:42:25,253
How long will you be?

1117
01:42:25,455 --> 01:42:27,844
About three to six months, I guess.

1118
01:45:16,215 --> 01:45:18,092
I hope you were the groom.

1119
01:45:21,175 --> 01:45:24,770
Ted Nugent called.
He wants his shirt back.

1120
01:45:32,095 --> 01:45:36,293
Thirteen million and you drive
this piece of shit to pick me up?

1121
01:45:36,495 --> 01:45:38,247
I blew it all on the suit.

1122
01:45:38,455 --> 01:45:42,494
- Where are they?
- Back row, silver sedan. Ten o'clock.

1123
01:45:42,735 --> 01:45:46,330
I picked up your personal
effects. Hope you don't mind.

1124
01:45:48,735 --> 01:45:51,090
I'm not sure these belong to me.

1125
01:46:01,575 --> 01:46:02,974
- Hi.
- Hi.

1126
01:46:03,175 --> 01:46:04,449
Rusty needs a girl.

1127
01:46:04,655 --> 01:46:07,374
There's a women's
prison down the road.

1128
01:46:08,935 --> 01:46:10,891
You said that you sold this.

1129
01:46:11,095 --> 01:46:12,653
I said that.

1130
01:46:12,935 --> 01:46:14,334
Liar.

1131
01:46:15,975 --> 01:46:17,294
Thief.

